This is a plugin for Haraka. Haraka is a Node.js email server.  For more information please visit https://haraka.github.io .
The core function of this plugin is to manage the identities feature of PlusPrivacy.

To get it up and running you need to go through the following steps:

1. Setup the PlusPrivacy coreServer,
2. Install Haraka
3. Acquire a SSL pair of certificate and private key. See the tls plugin information for more details.
4. Enable the DKIM feature. For the specific steps please see the dkim_sign plugin description.
5. Generate a secret key to use when encrypting conversations. Add the path to it in the operando.ini file.
6. Start the server by running "haraka -c /path/to/emailServer"


